<subSubSection id="ACA76575FFBB4248D4A71328FBE7F8D5" pageId="1" pageNumber="430" type="description">
<paragraph id="E40236FEFFBB4248D4A71328FD18F966" blockId="1.[151,1436,1552,2025]" pageId="1" pageNumber="430">
<emphasis id="D6C9EAECFFBB4248D4A71328FEC0F9CE" bold="true" box="[151,290,1552,1575]" pageId="1" pageNumber="430">Description.</emphasis>
Body length (including forewing): ♂, 
<quantity id="23459B1BFFBB4248D6F01328FCF7F9CE" box="[704,789,1552,1575]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.2" pageId="1" pageNumber="430" unit="mm" value="6.2">6.2 mm</quantity>
. Crown (
<figureCitation id="7C862A7BFFBB4248D7471328FC37F9CE" box="[887,981,1552,1575]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 10" captionStartId="2.[151,258,1952,1974]" captionTargetBox="[180,1401,195,1942]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[172,1403,191,1947]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 10. Pythamus hainanensis sp. nov.: 1. male habitus, dorsal view; 2. male habitus, lateral view; 3. male head, dorsal view; 4. male face; 5. male head, lateral view; 6. aedeagus, lateral view; 7. aedeagus, connective and style, ventral view; 8. subgenital plate, ventral view; 9. male genital capsule, lateral view; 10. male pygofer side, ventral-lateral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/235241/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="430">Figs 1, 3</figureCitation>
) with off-white markings on lateral carina and submarginal carina. Median longitudinal carina of frontoclypeus lamellate in upper half (
<figureCitation id="7C862A7BFFBB4248D0B1130AFB00F9A0" box="[1153,1250,1586,1609]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 10" captionStartId="2.[151,258,1952,1974]" captionTargetBox="[180,1401,195,1942]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[172,1403,191,1947]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 10. Pythamus hainanensis sp. nov.: 1. male habitus, dorsal view; 2. male habitus, lateral view; 3. male head, dorsal view; 4. male face; 5. male head, lateral view; 6. aedeagus, lateral view; 7. aedeagus, connective and style, ventral view; 8. subgenital plate, ventral view; 9. male genital capsule, lateral view; 10. male pygofer side, ventral-lateral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/235241/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="430">Figs 3, 5</figureCitation>
). Forewing (
<figureCitation id="7C862A7BFFBB4248D15C130AFF24F985" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 10" captionStartId="2.[151,258,1952,1974]" captionTargetBox="[180,1401,195,1942]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[172,1403,191,1947]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 10. Pythamus hainanensis sp. nov.: 1. male habitus, dorsal view; 2. male habitus, lateral view; 3. male head, dorsal view; 4. male face; 5. male head, lateral view; 6. aedeagus, lateral view; 7. aedeagus, connective and style, ventral view; 8. subgenital plate, ventral view; 9. male genital capsule, lateral view; 10. male pygofer side, ventral-lateral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/235241/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="430">Figs 1, 2</figureCitation>
) brown and translucent, marked with dark chocolate brown stripes in middle and end part, and two white semicircular spots in outer and inner margin respectively.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="E40236FEFFBB4248D4F713A2FBE7F8D5" blockId="1.[151,1436,1552,2025]" pageId="1" pageNumber="430">
Male pygofer (
<figureCitation id="7C862A7BFFBB4248D55C13A2FE4DF958" box="[364,431,1690,1713]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 10" captionStartId="2.[151,258,1952,1974]" captionTargetBox="[180,1401,195,1942]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[172,1403,191,1947]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 10. Pythamus hainanensis sp. nov.: 1. male habitus, dorsal view; 2. male habitus, lateral view; 3. male head, dorsal view; 4. male face; 5. male head, lateral view; 6. aedeagus, lateral view; 7. aedeagus, connective and style, ventral view; 8. subgenital plate, ventral view; 9. male genital capsule, lateral view; 10. male pygofer side, ventral-lateral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/235241/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="430">
Fig. 
<number id="527524D9FFBB4248D59113A2FE4DF958" box="[417,431,1690,1713]" pageId="1" pageNumber="430" value="9.0">9</number>
</figureCitation>
) posteriorly narrowed along caudo-ventral margin. Pygofer ventral process (
<figureCitation id="7C862A7BFFBB4248D0CB13A2FAA9F958" box="[1275,1355,1690,1713]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 10" captionStartId="2.[151,258,1952,1974]" captionTargetBox="[180,1401,195,1942]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[172,1403,191,1947]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 10. Pythamus hainanensis sp. nov.: 1. male habitus, dorsal view; 2. male habitus, lateral view; 3. male head, dorsal view; 4. male face; 5. male head, lateral view; 6. aedeagus, lateral view; 7. aedeagus, connective and style, ventral view; 8. subgenital plate, ventral view; 9. male genital capsule, lateral view; 10. male pygofer side, ventral-lateral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/235241/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="430">
Fig. 
<number id="527524D9FFBB4248D10013A2FAA9F958" box="[1328,1355,1690,1713]" pageId="1" pageNumber="430" value="10.0">10</number>
</figureCitation>
) rather straight, slightly shorter than pygofer, with about 
<number id="527524D9FFBB4248D6FE1385FD39F93D" box="[718,731,1725,1748]" pageId="1" pageNumber="430" value="3.0">3</number>
toothed processes distally. Aedeagus (
<figureCitation id="7C862A7BFFBB4248D0A21385FB1EF93D" box="[1170,1276,1725,1748]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 10" captionStartId="2.[151,258,1952,1974]" captionTargetBox="[180,1401,195,1942]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[172,1403,191,1947]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 10. Pythamus hainanensis sp. nov.: 1. male habitus, dorsal view; 2. male habitus, lateral view; 3. male head, dorsal view; 4. male face; 5. male head, lateral view; 6. aedeagus, lateral view; 7. aedeagus, connective and style, ventral view; 8. subgenital plate, ventral view; 9. male genital capsule, lateral view; 10. male pygofer side, ventral-lateral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/235241/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="430">Figs 6, 7</figureCitation>
) with bilobed apodeme arising from atrium and extended dorsolaterad; shaft long, apex hooked, subapex with a pair of lateral processes, like an arrow in ventral view; gonopore apical. Style (
<figureCitation id="7C862A7BFFBB4248D7B0123AFC24F8F0" box="[896,966,1794,1817]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 10" captionStartId="2.[151,258,1952,1974]" captionTargetBox="[180,1401,195,1942]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[172,1403,191,1947]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 10. Pythamus hainanensis sp. nov.: 1. male habitus, dorsal view; 2. male habitus, lateral view; 3. male head, dorsal view; 4. male face; 5. male head, lateral view; 6. aedeagus, lateral view; 7. aedeagus, connective and style, ventral view; 8. subgenital plate, ventral view; 9. male genital capsule, lateral view; 10. male pygofer side, ventral-lateral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/235241/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="430">
Fig. 
<number id="527524D9FFBB4248D787123AFC24F8F0" box="[951,966,1794,1817]" pageId="1" pageNumber="430" value="7.0">7</number>
</figureCitation>
), with footlike apex of apophysis having elongated lateral angle, apodeme apex rounded. Subgenital plate (
<figureCitation id="7C862A7BFFBB4248D765121DFC71F8D5" box="[853,915,1829,1852]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 10" captionStartId="2.[151,258,1952,1974]" captionTargetBox="[180,1401,195,1942]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[172,1403,191,1947]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 10. Pythamus hainanensis sp. nov.: 1. male habitus, dorsal view; 2. male habitus, lateral view; 3. male head, dorsal view; 4. male face; 5. male head, lateral view; 6. aedeagus, lateral view; 7. aedeagus, connective and style, ventral view; 8. subgenital plate, ventral view; 9. male genital capsule, lateral view; 10. male pygofer side, ventral-lateral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/235241/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="430">
Fig. 
<number id="527524D9FFBB4248D7B6121DFC71F8D5" box="[902,915,1829,1852]" pageId="1" pageNumber="430" value="8.0">8</number>
</figureCitation>
) elongate.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
